H0.text: Twins consisting of one boy and one girl, such as Mark and Carol Thatcher, are called what. Mixed Duo

H1.text: Twins consisting of one boy and one girl, such as Mark and Carol Thatcher, are called what. Binary Twins

H2.text: Twins consisting of one boy and one girl, such as Mark and Carol Thatcher, are called what. Hetero Twins

H3.text: Twins consisting of one boy and one girl, such as Mark and Carol Thatcher, are called what. Pigeon Pair

A4.text: Dizygotic twins from biracial couples can sometimes be mixed twins, which exhibit differing ethnic and racial features.

A5.text: This phenomenon is known as heteropaternal superfecundation.

A6.text: One 1992 study estimates that the frequency of heteropaternal superfecundation among dizygotic twins, whose parents were involved in paternity suits, was approximately 2.4%.
